4:
The perfect advertisement is one
that resonates with the heart.
5:
At Code Individual, we go above
and beyond to create ads that do
just that. For inquiries, please
contact—
14:
I think I heard Bulleta and Love
talking about it once. Said it was an
unusual sort of company, or
something...
16:
Apparently it isn't affiliated with
Noxel Group or AltMeme—
18:
Hey there, heroes! It's a pleasure to
finally meet you.
21:
Care to lend me a hand? Things
have gotten a little dicey out here.
25: Th-this ain't no time for small talk!
30:
Oh, dear. I forgot to introduce myself
first, didn't I?
34:
The name's Quinvere, founder and
CEO of Code Individual!
37:
You saw my ad a minute ago, right?
I also do a bit of modelling on the
side!
42:
And what the hell do these guys
want with a model or president or
whatever?!
47:
Wow, you guys are pretty
spectacular!
51:
More? What the heck did you do to
them?!
54:
Oh, just, you know... Made them a
little cranky.
56:
So what if I stole a teensy bit of info
from Noxel and weakened
AltMeme's position... and created
startups to interfere with AltMeme's
startups? Nothing wrong with that,
right?
68:
It's part of my ongoing goal to beat
my previous high score in life!
78:
Welcome to CI's Advertising Airship!
Happy to have you aboard!
81: Not like we had much of a choice...
84:
Heh, you're all pretty famous, you
know. I simply couldn't pass up the
chance to meet my heroes.
89:
...Someone told me once that
companies unaffiliated with Noxel
Group or AltMeme don't last too long.
92: Yes! And that's why I need your help.
95:
The fuddy-duddies at Noxel are as
stuck-up as they are stubborn.
AltMeme sacks anyone the instant
they don't fit into a spreadsheet...
97:
Don't you think Qualia City would be
more interesting if there was a little
more variety?
99:
I'll take the boring conventions of
this world and smash them to
pieces... Even more spectacularly
than the heroes who shot a hole
through the sky!
102:
...I think you've done quite a lot
already.
106:
Not nearly enough, though! Did you
see those guys earlier? They're dead
set on snuffing out any outside
competition.
108:
But all this makes for the perfect
opportunity to beat my current high
score in life. I just have to look at
things that way.
113:
By "high score"... Are you referring to
fulfilling your desire to change
society?
117:
Such a limited scope wouldn't be
nearly enough motivation for me.
121:
I'm talking about experiencing
something beyond what I can
imagine right now... Something that
brings me more joy than anything
before it. That's what I'm talking
about!
131:
Reaching greater heights than the
last is what matters most to me. But
I need friends like you to help me
get there.
133:
If anyone's capable of taking on the
world, it's you guys.
136:
Oh, but don't you worry! I've got
plenty in store to make it worth your
while.
146:
It looks like these guys were trying to
figure out who you are. They're from
AltMeme, no doubt...
148:
They're not the only weirdos looking
for you either... But you know that
already, don't you?
152:
...Just how much do you know about
us?
155:
Hehe. I prefer to know everything I
can about people I take a liking to.
158:
Go to hell! You're spilling your
secrets... NOW!
168:
I'll be protecting these fine folk from
here on out. If you want them, you'll
have to get through me first!
172:
Uh... Th-thanks? But you don't need
to do that... We can just hand them
over to the police and be done with
it...
176:
No need! You'll be safe and I'll have
fun. Win-win, right?
179:
So don't hold back, got it? Come
crush me and burn my company to
the ground by any means
necessary.
181:
Barriers, opposition, pain, tragedy...
The greatest joy in life is found in
overcoming these obstacles.
184:
Heh. I can't wait to see what kind of
high score you might set for yourself!
187:
Take some time to collect yourself
before coming to see me again. I'll
be waiting for you!
190:
Oh? I thought you guys would be
used to this sort of thing by now.
Was I wrong?
195:
I can't say I've ever enjoyed it
anywhere near as much as you
have...
199:
...Heh, it's hard to believe you still
haven't run off.
203:
I'm as interested in you guys as all
these weirdos chasing you! Let's be
friends!
207:
Are you giving us the chance to say
no?
212:
That's right! I don't want to force you
to do anything.
215:
But I've still got to take my shot,
right? It's not in my DNA to give up
on people I like!
234:
...This might just score the highest on
the list of places I've been to!
237:
Can you hear it? My heartbeat's
going into overdrive right now!
240:
I'll be sure to thank you for this later!
Now then, how about we set a few
new high scores together?
